        Ear Microsuction Specialists
    We specialise in the microsuction ear wax removal technique for removing ear blockages. This is generally accepted to be the safest and most effective method of ear wax removal, and it is
    completely syringe free with no need for weeks of softening with oil. The procedure commonly takes a few minutes for each ear. In some rare cases, ear syringing can still be effective, and some
    of our audiologists may still recommend and use this procedure where appropriate.








        Local & Professional
    Carried out at one of our many convenient ear wax clinics or in your home, we charge from £40 for one ear and £60 for both ears (unless otherwise stated on the Ear Wax Clinic Locations
    page). Some ear wax removal clinics are able to make emergency evening and weekend appointments. A few ear wax removal specialists also offer home visits for an
    additional fee. There will be a video otoscopic examination before and after the procedure to show you the results. If the problem isn't a blocked ear, then a hearing test may be carried out
    and/or referral advice may be given, charged at the normal appointment rate.








        Registered & Insured
    Safety is paramount, and the ear wax removal procedure should always be comfortable and pain-free. We carefully select fully qualified and registered experienced ear care professionals who are
    also trained to The Hearing Lab's standards as well as their registering body's standards. If they have not been trained by The Hearing Lab, this is because they have been previously trained by
    another Hearing Lab-recognised training provider. We have also worked closely with insurance providers to make sure our practitioners and their patients are fully covered.













